          #### The problem

          Most customers will have 1000s of files stored on their GNARBOX, so how do you organise all of this media? The traditional way is to create folders, name them, then add files to these folders. But, this method suits desktop more than mobile, because you have a mouse and large keyboard.

          Additionally, let’s imagine that you’re skiing, and you want to quickly backup your files. You’re in the mountains, so it’s <em>unlikely that you want to spend time creating folders and organising your files</em>. You just want to backup your media and get back to skiing! You can always organise your files later when you’re connected to a laptop.

